in july 2004 the board of directors approved the adoption of the 2004 stock option plan. the 2004 stock option plan provides for the grant of
options to purchase up to 500,000 shares of milestones common stock. options may be granted to employees, officers, directors and consultants of milestone for the purchase of common stock of milestone at a price not less than the fair market
value of the common stock on the date of the grant. in general, options become exercisable over a three-year period from the grant date and expire five years after the date of grant. no options were exercised in 2011.
in march 2008, the board of directors authorized an additional 250,000 options to this plan.
